# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — thermal-sandbox (v0 archive)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Goal: commit the CODE, DOCS, and small REFERENCE inputs; exclude the ~1 GB of
# regenerable simulation OUTPUTS and throwaway debug data.
#
# NOTE: this encodes a data-retention choice (see .agent/handoff/03_consolidation_
# recommendations.md, Rec. 5). Ignored simulation results will NOT be in the repo.
# If you need them preserved, use git-LFS or an external store instead of ignoring.
#
# (git does not support trailing comments on pattern lines — keep them on their own.)
# =============================================================================

# ---- OS / editor cruft ------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
.idea/
.vscode/

# ---- Python -----------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ---- Generated simulation outputs (by type, anywhere) -----------------------
# *.feather = raytracing irradiance (regenerable); *.pkl = pickled results;
# *.oct = Radiance octrees (regenerable from scene .rad); *.zip = output bundles.
*.feather
*.pkl
*.oct
*.zip

# ---- Oversized media --------------------------------------------------------
# 110 MB figure source; GitHub rejects files >100 MB outright.
*.tiff
*.tif

# ---- Throwaway / debug directories ------------------------------------------
src_archive/debug_outputs/
src_archive/debug_raytracing_results/
src_archive/grid_records/debug_*
# older outputs + superseded db (doubly archived):
src_archive/archive/

# ---- Regenerable result directories -----------------------------------------
src_archive/raytracing_results/
src_archive/outputs/

# Keep the human-readable report; drop the heavy per-scenario CSVs + plots.
src_archive/analysis_outputs/*
!src_archive/analysis_outputs/analysis_report.md

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL — heavy model-source binaries (JUDGMENT CALL)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These are NOT cheaply regenerable (the Rhino model, Honeybee model, Radiance
# scene geometry). They're reference for rebuilding v1, but large (.3dm ~45 MB,
# .hbjson ~34 MB, envelope.rad ~9 MB) and trip GitHub's 50 MB warning. Left
# COMMITTED by default; uncomment to exclude or move to git-LFS instead.
# =============================================================================
# *.3dm
# *.hbjson
# **/scene/envelope.rad
